itemLabel: Arthur Vere Harvey, Baron Harvey of Prestbury

wikipedia_page.main: Arthur Vere Harvey, Baron Harvey of Prestbury,  (31 January 1906 – 5 April 1994) was a senior Royal Air Force officer and a British Conservative politician who served as a Member of Parliament (MP) for 26 years.
